# Adding a slide — workflow

When the user says "add a slide about X" or "add a megastat slide for Y":

## Step 1 — Pick the layout

Match the user's intent to one of these layouts. If it's ambiguous, ask
which one they want:

- **Headline + bullets** → standard content slide (template slide 4)
- **One huge number** → megastat (template slide 5)
- **Several small stats** → `.row-3` or `.row-4` of `.stat` (NEXO deck slide 3)
- **Code example** → `.code` block (template slide 6)
- **Before/after comparison** → `.cmp` table (template slide 7)
- **Three or four feature cards** → `.row-3`/`.row-4` of `.card` (template slide 8)
- **Pull-quote / one-liner** → centered quote slide (template slide 9)
- **Section divider** → dark slide with section number (template slide 3)

## Step 2 — Read the closest example

**Before generating any HTML**, read the matching source slide in
`template/index.html`. Copy its structure verbatim — chrome, classes,
inline styles, everything.

If a closer match exists in `examples/cursor-nexo-security/index.html`
(e.g. for `.bug` pills, `.row-step`, `.qr-card`, `.partner-logo`), use
that as the source instead.

## Step 3 — Decide the position

Slides are linear `<section>` blocks. Ask the user where to insert if
unclear. Default: append before the closing slide.

## Step 4 — Generate the new `<section>`

- Pick the right `.slide` vs `.slide.dark` class.
- Pick the matching logo variant (`*_LIGHT.png` vs `*_DARK.png`).
- Write the eyebrow (short, uppercase-styled by `theme.css`).
- Fill the body using only the layout helpers from `theme.css`.
- Add speaker notes in `<aside class="notes">…</aside>`.
- Set the footer counter to its new position.

## Step 5 — Update counters

Critical: this is the easy-to-miss step.

- Bump every following slide's `NN` counter by 1.
- Update every slide's `MM` total to the new total.

Example: deck has 10 slides, you insert at position 5. Old slide 5
becomes slide 6, …, old slide 10 becomes slide 11. Every slide's `MM`
goes from `10` to `11`.

The fastest way: open the file, search for `/ 10` and replace with
`/ 11`, then search for `0N / 11` (where N is the inserted position)
and bump each subsequent counter individually.

## Step 6 — Verify

- Run `npm run present:template` (or `:example`).
- Open `localhost:4321`.
- Press `O` for overview — confirm the new slide appears in the right
  position with correct chrome.
- Press `→` and `←` around it — confirm transitions work.

## Common mistakes

- ❌ Skipping step 5 (footer counters drift).
- ❌ Wrong logo variant (light logo on dark slide → invisible).
- ❌ Hardcoded colors (`color: #ff0000` instead of `color: var(--accent)`).
- ❌ Missing `<aside class="notes">` — speaker mode shows blank.
- ❌ Editing `examples/cursor-nexo-security/` when the user meant
  `template/`. The example is preserved as a historical reference.
